article.headline: Rice 81, Lamar 75
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Michael Harris scored 21 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for Rice, which beat Lamar 81-75 on Thursday night. J.R. Harrison added 19 points on 9-of-11 shooting for the Owls (5-1). Brock Gillespie had 13, and Jason McKrieth scored 11. Alan Daniels led Lamar with a game-high 24 points and 10 rebounds. Raymond Anthony scored 15 points for the Cardinals (4-3), and Jason Grant had 11. Lamar outrebounded Rice 49-36 and built a 32-29 halftime lead but was plagued by poor shooting. The Cardinals shot less than 37 percent from the field for the game, while Rice shot nearly 53 percent. Lamar launched 28 3-pointers, hitting only 10.
